1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,980
=Episode 16=

3
00:01:39,780 --> 00:01:40,220
Zhangzhu.

4
00:01:42,620 --> 00:01:42,940
Ms. Lin.

5
00:01:43,177 --> 00:01:44,940
Help me book a nearby French restaurant.

6
00:01:45,060 --> 00:01:46,420
7 PM tonight, a table for two.

7
00:01:47,980 --> 00:01:48,380
Okay.

8
00:01:51,940 --> 00:01:52,620
Anything else?

9
00:01:53,555 --> 00:01:54,866
Who am I going with, right?

10
00:01:55,300 --> 00:01:55,940
With He Han.

11
00:01:57,060 --> 00:01:58,020
I thought so.

12
00:01:58,420 --> 00:02:00,060
Mr. He Han likes French food.

13
00:02:00,155 --> 00:02:01,800
You have really taken your idol-chasing

14
00:02:01,888 --> 00:02:02,955
to a very detailed level.

15
00:02:03,100 --> 00:02:03,940
If you are a true fan,

16
00:02:03,940 --> 00:02:05,711
you have to know
everything from head to toe.

17
00:02:05,711 --> 00:02:06,911
Only then does it count.

18
00:02:07,340 --> 00:02:08,460
What kind of fan is that?

19
00:02:08,580 --> 00:02:09,822
You are just being ridiculous.

20
00:02:20,620 --> 00:02:21,488
There is something

21
00:02:21,860 --> 00:02:22,940
I think I have found a lead.

22
00:02:25,688 --> 00:02:26,688
Whose problem is it?

23
00:02:27,340 --> 00:02:27,940
It's Fragile.

24
00:02:29,580 --> 00:02:31,422
Among the new authors I referred to her,

25
00:02:32,260 --> 00:02:33,020
the first five

26
00:02:33,020 --> 00:02:34,780
had contact
with Zhao Lanxin's company.

27
00:02:35,300 --> 00:02:36,900
So, how do we handle her?

28
00:02:39,666 --> 00:02:40,666
Let's wait and see.

29
00:02:40,822 --> 00:02:41,711
Wait for what?

30
00:02:47,111 --> 00:02:48,840
For tonight's
French restaurant reservation,

31
00:02:48,866 --> 00:02:50,066
have Fragile make it.

32
00:02:50,220 --> 00:02:50,620
Why?

33
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:52,620
She knows the manager there.

34
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:56,020
Got it.

35
00:03:22,620 --> 00:03:23,260
Welcome.

36
00:03:23,422 --> 00:03:25,666
Sir, would you like to
see what flowers we have?

37
00:03:25,940 --> 00:03:26,340
Roses.

38
00:03:26,780 --> 00:03:27,340
Roses.

39
00:03:27,420 --> 00:03:28,390
What color would you like?

40
00:03:28,580 --> 00:03:29,140
Red.

41
00:03:29,511 --> 00:03:30,540
How many would you like?

42
00:03:31,222 --> 00:03:32,444
The more, the better.

43
00:03:32,900 --> 00:03:33,660
I want the kind

44
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:34,700
where people see me

45
00:03:34,700 --> 00:03:36,266
and know I am deeply in love.

46
00:03:36,270 --> 00:03:37,720
Make it as over the top as possible.

47
00:03:37,740 --> 00:03:38,620
Alright, got it.

48
00:03:38,666 --> 00:03:40,610
Sir, you are really
straightforward and generous.

49
00:03:40,620 --> 00:03:41,740
Would you like to add a card?

50
00:03:41,940 --> 00:03:42,700
No need for a card.

51
00:03:42,900 --> 00:03:43,980
Just give me an invoice.

52
00:04:11,100 --> 00:04:12,060
Next time, we will go eat

53
00:04:12,088 --> 00:04:13,470
at that noodle place I told you about.

54
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:15,060
Mr. He, waiting for our boss?

55
00:04:15,355 --> 00:04:16,300
Is she off work yet?

56
00:04:16,977 --> 00:04:19,370
Ms. Lin just finished
a meeting with the publicity team.

57
00:04:19,370 --> 00:04:20,000
She will be down soon.

58
00:04:20,010 --> 00:04:20,660
Okay.

59
00:04:20,740 --> 00:04:21,650
We will head out first.

60
00:04:22,060 --> 00:04:22,380
Bye.

61
00:04:22,460 --> 00:04:23,630
We are leaving first, Mr. He.

62
00:04:24,311 --> 00:04:25,311
These flowers look great.

63
00:04:33,266 --> 00:04:34,155
They are for you.

64
00:04:34,660 --> 00:04:35,600
Isn't this too much?

65
00:04:35,860 --> 00:04:37,220
That is how I show sincerity.

66
00:04:38,444 --> 00:04:39,760
You should not have spent so much.

67
00:04:52,380 --> 00:04:53,260
I got you an invoice.

68
00:05:02,300 --> 00:05:03,266
What are you looking at?

69
00:05:05,900 --> 00:05:06,780
Nothing.

70
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:08,700
Mr. He Han took Ms. Lin out for dinner.

71
00:05:10,844 --> 00:05:12,900
Our company
is going to be sold to Dingqi Platform.

72
00:05:13,020 --> 00:05:13,900
You know that, right?

73
00:05:15,100 --> 00:05:17,340
Mr. Fan will become our boss's boss.

74
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:22,380
I am just reminding
you to be more careful.

75
00:05:22,780 --> 00:05:24,620
You are always
following Ms. Lin around,

76
00:05:24,620 --> 00:05:25,977
back and forth, everywhere.

77
00:05:26,022 --> 00:05:27,500
In the future, when you see Mr. Fan,

78
00:05:28,060 --> 00:05:30,020
find chances to show yourself.

79
00:05:30,300 --> 00:05:30,980
Plan ahead.

80
00:05:32,020 --> 00:05:32,340
Okay.

81
00:05:33,140 --> 00:05:34,100
Thank you, Fragile.

82
00:05:34,155 --> 00:05:35,266
Please look out for me.

83
00:05:35,288 --> 00:05:36,540
It is nothing. I am leaving.

84
00:05:48,460 --> 00:05:49,700
You picked a good spot.

85
00:05:49,900 --> 00:05:51,600
People can see us clearly from outside.

86
00:05:55,020 --> 00:05:56,580
How long do you plan to sit here?

87
00:05:57,420 --> 00:05:59,380
I need to go back
early today to call Gu Yan.

88
00:05:59,422 --> 00:06:00,500
He is not in a good state.

89
00:06:00,780 --> 00:06:02,180
At least three hours.

90
00:06:02,355 --> 00:06:04,377
If we are putting on a show,
we have to go all the way.

91
00:06:04,860 --> 00:06:06,580
But we cannot possibly talk that long.

92
00:06:06,820 --> 00:06:07,660
Why not?

93
00:06:07,740 --> 00:06:09,340
I have plenty to share with you.

94
00:06:10,755 --> 00:06:12,400
Even three hours feels short to me.

95
00:06:13,500 --> 00:06:14,300
Ms. Lin.

96
00:06:14,820 --> 00:06:15,740
Mr. He.

97
00:06:19,140 --> 00:06:19,860
New boyfriend?

98
00:06:20,666 --> 00:06:21,900
He has always been this one.

99
00:06:21,900 --> 00:06:23,300
They are seriously dating.

100
00:06:23,777 --> 00:06:25,600
They probably think the same about us.

101
00:06:31,260 --> 00:06:32,340
Here, have some cod.

102
00:06:36,133 --> 00:06:37,111
Open your mouth.

103
00:06:52,500 --> 00:06:53,420
Thanks.

104
00:06:54,020 --> 00:06:55,820
You know I hate carrots.

105
00:07:02,540 --> 00:07:03,580
I came here to help you.

106
00:07:03,740 --> 00:07:06,177
Even if there is no return,
you still treat me like this.

107
00:07:06,700 --> 00:07:08,140
How do you know there is no return?

108
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:09,577
What did you give me in return?

109
00:07:20,555 --> 00:07:22,733
You're too proactive.
Won't it look too deliberate?

110
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:25,088
You should sit a bit closer to me now.

111
00:07:25,140 --> 00:07:26,777
Otherwise, it will not look real.

112
00:07:35,780 --> 00:07:37,580
This is exactly why
I came to see you today.

113
00:07:41,580 --> 00:07:42,620
Flip to the back.

114
00:07:46,420 --> 00:07:48,420
There are photos of
the nursing home where he lives

115
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:50,700
and his daily routine.

116
00:07:52,540 --> 00:07:53,340
You have been there?

117
00:07:56,711 --> 00:07:57,860
You should go take a look, too.

118
00:07:59,460 --> 00:08:00,700
Isn't this good enough?

119
00:08:04,533 --> 00:08:06,420
The caregiver said
he often loses his temper

120
00:08:06,580 --> 00:08:07,622
and argues with people.

121
00:08:07,980 --> 00:08:09,980
So now, some public entertainment places

122
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:12,500
don't allow him in anymore.

123
00:08:12,660 --> 00:08:13,500
That is normal.

124
00:08:13,555 --> 00:08:14,860
Has he not always been like that?

125
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:16,700
Nothing pleases him.

126
00:08:16,700 --> 00:08:17,955
He is unhappy wherever he goes.

127
00:08:18,288 --> 00:08:19,980
Honestly, he should not
be in a nursing home.

128
00:08:19,980 --> 00:08:21,020
He should be in prison.

129
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:23,980
His health is not good.

130
00:08:26,900 --> 00:08:27,420
Liver cancer.

131
00:08:29,533 --> 00:08:31,377
When he came to see you that time,

132
00:08:31,844 --> 00:08:33,666
he had probably already been diagnosed.

133
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:36,180
He refuses treatment.

134
00:08:37,660 --> 00:08:38,900
He only took some painkillers.

135
00:08:40,533 --> 00:08:42,888
The caregiver tried to get
him to quit smoking and drinking,

136
00:08:45,420 --> 00:08:46,410
but it did not work.

137
00:08:46,410 --> 00:08:47,622
Of course, it did not work.

138
00:08:48,088 --> 00:08:49,180
No one can persuade him.

139
00:08:49,333 --> 00:08:50,860
He will drink until the day he dies.

140
00:08:51,622 --> 00:08:53,888
I told him to come back
to Shanghai for treatment.

141
00:08:55,140 --> 00:08:57,420
Cancer is not
necessarily untreatable now.

142
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:59,060
At the very least, it could improve

143
00:08:59,060 --> 00:09:00,180
his quality of life.

144
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:06,180
But seeing him like this,

145
00:09:08,700 --> 00:09:10,060
if no one looks after him,

146
00:09:13,420 --> 00:09:14,700
he won't have much time left.

147
00:09:17,660 --> 00:09:18,580
That is good news.

148
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:20,620
We should celebrate.

149
00:09:21,260 --> 00:09:23,140
One less disaster in this world.

150
00:09:23,577 --> 00:09:24,420
Even if he changes...

151
00:09:24,420 --> 00:09:25,780
I know what you are going to say.

152
00:09:25,888 --> 00:09:28,170
You are going to say no matter what,
he is still my father.

153
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:30,111
Without him, there would be no me.

154
00:09:30,380 --> 00:09:30,980
I know.

155
00:09:32,100 --> 00:09:34,140
You have said that to me for ten years.

156
00:09:37,340 --> 00:09:38,220
So you think

157
00:09:38,780 --> 00:09:40,660
just because he is sick and dying,

158
00:09:41,620 --> 00:09:42,580
I should forgive him?

159
00:09:44,380 --> 00:09:45,020
Why?

160
00:09:46,180 --> 00:09:48,060
When he put me
through all that back then,

161
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:49,900
he should have thought about today.

162
00:10:03,060 --> 00:10:05,300
Not everyone in this world
deserves to be a father.

163
00:10:06,577 --> 00:10:08,355
You don't need to
worry about him anymore.

164
00:10:09,044 --> 00:10:10,977
And you don't need
to go see him anymore.

165
00:10:11,622 --> 00:10:12,844
He is not worth it.

166
00:10:28,660 --> 00:10:29,340
Do you know,

167
00:10:30,660 --> 00:10:32,340
when you said that just now,

168
00:10:35,222 --> 00:10:36,820
you sounded exactly like your father.

169
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:49,620
He has already bought his burial plot.

170
00:10:50,980 --> 00:10:52,340
He sent me the contract.

171
00:10:54,180 --> 00:10:55,420
He chose the cheapest one.

172
00:10:57,540 --> 00:10:59,300
He said he knows no one will visit him.

173
00:11:04,180 --> 00:11:05,260
He told me all this

174
00:11:08,860 --> 00:11:10,140
so you would know.

175
00:11:15,980 --> 00:11:21,020
(Grave Purchase Agreement)

176
00:12:05,260 --> 00:12:06,266
What are you doing?

177
00:12:08,100 --> 00:12:09,060
Turning the tide.

178
00:12:10,460 --> 00:12:12,580
Everyone now thinks
we are back together.

179
00:12:36,088 --> 00:12:37,377
I will drink as a penalty.

180
00:12:42,755 --> 00:12:44,711
The next song is
specially requested by Mr. He

181
00:12:44,755 --> 00:12:46,700
for Ms. Lin beside him.

182
00:12:47,940 --> 00:12:48,660
This is the song

183
00:12:48,660 --> 00:12:50,380
that played in the car

184
00:12:50,422 --> 00:12:52,266
when Mr. He first drove Ms. Lin home.

185
00:13:01,220 --> 00:13:02,540
What first-time home?

186
00:13:02,540 --> 00:13:03,500
What in the car?

187
00:13:03,622 --> 00:13:04,933
How come I don't know about it?

188
00:13:05,020 --> 00:13:05,740
I made it up.

189
00:13:06,222 --> 00:13:07,570
One song costs over 200 yuan.

190
00:13:07,570 --> 00:13:09,577
It is fine. I already paid.
This one is on me.

191
00:13:14,620 --> 00:13:15,220
Sounds good.

192
00:13:38,100 --> 00:13:41,300
(Send to Dai Shan. Confirm.)

193
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,066
I will walk you upstairs.

194
00:14:06,660 --> 00:14:08,100
No need. I can go up myself.

195
00:14:08,820 --> 00:14:09,300
Don't move.

196
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:10,711
There is something there.

197
00:14:33,620 --> 00:14:34,260
Thank you

198
00:14:35,133 --> 00:14:36,933
for putting on this act with me today.

199
00:14:39,380 --> 00:14:40,820
Maybe I should go up with you.

200
00:14:44,540 --> 00:14:45,940
I have other things to do upstairs.

201
00:14:46,620 --> 00:14:47,060
Head back.

202
00:14:48,060 --> 00:14:48,740
See you tomorrow.

203
00:14:49,244 --> 00:14:50,355
We will talk tomorrow.

204
00:15:14,660 --> 00:15:15,620
Why didn't you come up?

205
00:15:15,911 --> 00:15:17,300
I saw everything from upstairs.

206
00:15:21,888 --> 00:15:23,460
I will walk around downstairs for a bit.

207
00:15:23,580 --> 00:15:24,420
I will come up later.

208
00:15:51,540 --> 00:15:52,700
Why did you come down?

209
00:15:53,333 --> 00:15:55,820
Zhangzhu is there.
Some things are not convenient to say.

210
00:15:58,140 --> 00:15:58,700
So?

211
00:16:00,220 --> 00:16:01,700
How did it feel revisiting the past?

212
00:16:06,460 --> 00:16:07,380
Acting is acting.

213
00:16:08,666 --> 00:16:10,340
You always pick
the best parts to perform.

214
00:16:11,180 --> 00:16:11,900
So, it was good.

215
00:16:15,580 --> 00:16:16,555
When we were good,

216
00:16:17,380 --> 00:16:18,580
we were really good.

217
00:16:20,140 --> 00:16:21,060
When we were not,

218
00:16:21,940 --> 00:16:22,780
it was really bad.

219
00:16:25,100 --> 00:16:26,300
So what we just showed

220
00:16:26,820 --> 00:16:28,100
was the best side of us.

221
00:16:29,888 --> 00:16:31,977
Then, do you think he
was acting or being real?

222
00:16:36,733 --> 00:16:37,933
I don't know.

223
00:16:39,220 --> 00:16:40,780
Do you want him to be acting or real?

224
00:16:43,580 --> 00:16:44,180
Why not

225
00:16:44,900 --> 00:16:46,660
take this chance

226
00:16:46,820 --> 00:16:47,940
to get back together?

227
00:16:48,755 --> 00:16:49,760
Everyone would be happy.

228
00:16:55,340 --> 00:16:56,700
Actually, being fake is not bad.

229
00:16:58,580 --> 00:16:59,420
There is no pressure

230
00:17:00,140 --> 00:17:00,940
or burden.

231
00:17:02,940 --> 00:17:04,460
No need to worry about

232
00:17:04,860 --> 00:17:06,660
fighting and making up again.

233
00:17:07,740 --> 00:17:08,780
It is exhausting.

234
00:18:13,420 --> 00:18:15,180
I have started reading your novels.

235
00:18:16,860 --> 00:18:17,660
While reading,

236
00:18:17,980 --> 00:18:19,220
I even discussed with Er Jiu

237
00:18:19,340 --> 00:18:20,020
what you wrote.

238
00:18:23,420 --> 00:18:25,860
Why are you interested in my novels?

239
00:18:25,940 --> 00:18:27,900
At first, it was confusing.

240
00:18:27,900 --> 00:18:29,620
But as I kept reading, I caught up.

241
00:18:31,020 --> 00:18:32,130
In the comments,

242
00:18:32,130 --> 00:18:34,540
people always compare you with He Han.

243
00:18:35,340 --> 00:18:36,810
I have read He Han's novels.

244
00:18:36,810 --> 00:18:38,420
I think you write better than he does.

245
00:18:42,580 --> 00:18:44,300
You might be the only one

246
00:18:44,688 --> 00:18:46,400
who thinks I write better than He Han.

247
00:18:55,260 --> 00:18:57,020
Did I disturb your writing?

248
00:18:58,180 --> 00:18:58,580
No.

249
00:18:59,140 --> 00:19:00,220
I have not started yet.

250
00:19:01,420 --> 00:19:02,260
Then, you go ahead.

251
00:19:02,420 --> 00:19:03,311
I will leave first.

252
00:19:09,700 --> 00:19:10,420
(Dingqi 2024 Annual Author Night,
Gu Yan)

253
00:19:10,420 --> 00:19:11,340
The trophy is back?

254
00:19:12,660 --> 00:19:13,500
It was delivered.

255
00:19:17,780 --> 00:19:19,600
Then, we should take a photo with it.

256
00:20:37,420 --> 00:20:38,533
You really went all out.

257
00:20:40,020 --> 00:20:41,060
You and Lin Zhanqiao

258
00:20:41,060 --> 00:20:43,340
had flowers

259
00:20:43,540 --> 00:20:45,060
and a candlelight dinner last night.

260
00:20:45,555 --> 00:20:47,200
Want me to get you a megaphone?

261
00:20:47,260 --> 00:20:49,266
So you can announce it
to the whole world.

262
00:20:54,700 --> 00:20:56,620
If I told you I wanted to make it real,

263
00:20:56,620 --> 00:20:57,866
would you believe me?

264
00:21:01,180 --> 00:21:03,340
Do you know who came to see me today?

265
00:21:05,020 --> 00:21:05,460
Mimi.

266
00:21:06,900 --> 00:21:08,340
Even she knows that

267
00:21:08,500 --> 00:21:11,580
you are getting back together
with Lin Zhanqiao.

268
00:21:12,300 --> 00:21:13,380
She thinks

269
00:21:13,380 --> 00:21:15,820
she and I are on the same side,

270
00:21:16,500 --> 00:21:19,740
both exes you let down.

271
00:21:20,644 --> 00:21:22,560
If you had not said it,
I would have forgotten.

272
00:21:22,660 --> 00:21:24,260
We have not officially broken up yet.

273
00:21:28,020 --> 00:21:28,580
Happy breakup.

274
00:21:28,955 --> 00:21:31,420
So easy that I almost
don't want to break up with you.

275
00:21:32,300 --> 00:21:34,060
Would she accept it

276
00:21:34,180 --> 00:21:35,540
if you asked Lin Zhanqiao

277
00:21:35,820 --> 00:21:37,300
to get back together?

278
00:21:38,220 --> 00:21:40,380
It is not my first time.
I have experience.

279
00:21:42,700 --> 00:21:45,380
So you like her more, right?

280
00:21:46,140 --> 00:21:47,810
Of course, she likes me more.

281
00:21:47,810 --> 00:21:48,990
So she carries a heavy burden.

282
00:21:49,060 --> 00:21:50,140
I am more relaxed.

283
00:21:50,140 --> 00:21:50,940
If I make the move

284
00:21:50,940 --> 00:21:52,420
and get rejected, it won't hurt much.

285
00:21:54,420 --> 00:21:57,020
That line might work on others,

286
00:21:57,420 --> 00:21:59,260
but not on me.

287
00:22:01,180 --> 00:22:02,580
If you're so attached,

288
00:22:02,580 --> 00:22:04,622
now that you've
finally gotten back together,

289
00:22:04,700 --> 00:22:05,900
why not fix your issues?

290
00:22:09,555 --> 00:22:11,688
If I were going to change,
I would have long ago.

291
00:22:15,540 --> 00:22:16,100
But honestly,

292
00:22:17,340 --> 00:22:19,340
you have known me for a while.

293
00:22:20,500 --> 00:22:21,900
Do you really think I am

294
00:22:21,900 --> 00:22:23,500
as messy in relationships as people say?

295
00:22:23,660 --> 00:22:24,140
Messy,

296
00:22:25,180 --> 00:22:26,020
but not chaotic.

297
00:22:26,340 --> 00:22:28,730
What I mean is you simply don't know

298
00:22:28,730 --> 00:22:30,860
how to handle relationships properly,

299
00:22:31,340 --> 00:22:33,460
yet you insist on acting like an expert.

300
00:22:35,060 --> 00:22:37,060
Come on,
how many people can do it right?

301
00:22:44,660 --> 00:22:45,780
Okay, one more step.

302
00:22:47,140 --> 00:22:47,500
Okay.

303
00:22:47,940 --> 00:22:48,620
This way.

304
00:22:49,940 --> 00:22:50,340
Grandma,

305
00:22:50,340 --> 00:22:52,260
the drive will take a bit longer today.

306
00:22:53,020 --> 00:22:54,740
You can listen to the radio on the way.

307
00:22:54,866 --> 00:22:56,620
I also brought you
some butterfly pastries.

308
00:22:56,620 --> 00:22:58,690
If you get hungry, you can have some.

309
00:22:58,690 --> 00:22:59,340
Okay.

310
00:23:00,620 --> 00:23:00,940
Alright.

311
00:23:01,060 --> 00:23:01,800
Grandma, step.

312
00:23:04,700 --> 00:23:05,340
Okay, sit tight.

313
00:23:05,500 --> 00:23:06,020
Alright.

314
00:23:07,488 --> 00:23:09,580
Grandma, are you thirsty?
Do you want some water?

315
00:23:09,860 --> 00:23:10,900
No, thanks.

316
00:23:11,340 --> 00:23:13,220
If you need anything later,
just tell me.

317
00:23:13,420 --> 00:23:14,860
Okay.

318
00:23:30,060 --> 00:23:30,780
Grandma, here.

319
00:23:31,066 --> 00:23:31,740
- Okay.
- No rush.

320
00:23:31,740 --> 00:23:32,500
Okay.

321
00:23:33,500 --> 00:23:34,460
We are almost there.

322
00:23:35,100 --> 00:23:35,500
Okay.

323
00:23:36,711 --> 00:23:37,780
This is fine to eat, right?

324
00:23:39,540 --> 00:23:41,500
Grandma, there is a small river nearby.

325
00:23:41,740 --> 00:23:43,380
Later, you can take a boat ride.

326
00:23:43,820 --> 00:23:44,220
Okay.

327
00:23:44,577 --> 00:23:45,460
You can walk here.

328
00:23:48,100 --> 00:23:48,580
Mom!

329
00:23:50,740 --> 00:23:51,700
That is your daughter?

330
00:23:52,060 --> 00:23:53,060
So beautiful.

331
00:23:53,200 --> 00:23:54,860
Your son-in-law is quite impressive too.

332
00:23:57,666 --> 00:23:58,260
We are here.

333
00:23:58,620 --> 00:23:58,940
Okay.

334
00:23:59,060 --> 00:23:59,660
You are here?

335
00:23:59,780 --> 00:24:00,140
Dad.

336
00:24:00,940 --> 00:24:01,460
Ling Yikai.

337
00:24:01,470 --> 00:24:02,100
Ling Yikai's grandma.

338
00:24:02,100 --> 00:24:02,822
- Hello.
- Hello.

339
00:24:03,020 --> 00:24:04,380
Grandma, this is my dad.

340
00:24:04,980 --> 00:24:06,090
Welcome, Grandma.

341
00:24:06,090 --> 00:24:06,900
(Baixing Restaurant)
Come, please come.

342
00:24:06,900 --> 00:24:07,990
Grandma, let's go inside.

343
00:24:08,260 --> 00:24:09,260
Careful, there are steps.

344
00:24:09,420 --> 00:24:09,700
Okay.

345
00:24:09,800 --> 00:24:10,780
Slowly, lift your foot.

346
00:24:10,980 --> 00:24:12,260
Grandma, have some tea.

347
00:24:12,740 --> 00:24:13,460
Okay.

348
00:24:14,740 --> 00:24:15,420
Ling,

349
00:24:15,660 --> 00:24:17,140
I am really sorry.

350
00:24:17,380 --> 00:24:19,100
For a first meeting between families,

351
00:24:19,540 --> 00:24:20,620
we should have picked

352
00:24:21,020 --> 00:24:22,300
a nicer restaurant.

353
00:24:23,260 --> 00:24:24,140
But as you can see,

354
00:24:24,140 --> 00:24:25,620
I need to keep an eye on the game room

355
00:24:25,620 --> 00:24:26,900
across the street.

356
00:24:27,140 --> 00:24:29,220
So we could only
come to this small place

357
00:24:29,288 --> 00:24:30,490
to have a simple meal together.

358
00:24:30,490 --> 00:24:31,660
Is that alright?

359
00:24:31,740 --> 00:24:32,580
Alright.

360
00:24:32,580 --> 00:24:34,820
Her mom will be done with
mahjong soon and come over.

361
00:24:35,422 --> 00:24:37,060
Let them know they can start cooking.

362
00:24:37,180 --> 00:24:37,540
Okay.

363
00:24:38,220 --> 00:24:38,620
Well,

364
00:24:39,140 --> 00:24:41,060
Ling, do you know how to play mahjong?

365
00:24:41,620 --> 00:24:42,340
I don't, Mr. Zhao.

366
00:24:42,377 --> 00:24:44,130
- Then, you should learn it properly.
- You can start cooking now.

367
00:24:44,140 --> 00:24:45,260
Life is like strong liquor.

368
00:24:45,460 --> 00:24:46,940
Mahjong eases a thousand worries.

369
00:24:47,340 --> 00:24:48,140
But don't worry.

370
00:24:48,380 --> 00:24:49,780
Lanxin will have time

371
00:24:50,020 --> 00:24:50,960
to teach you properly.

372
00:24:51,380 --> 00:24:55,311
Before my daughter could even talk,
she could already play mahjong.

373
00:24:55,700 --> 00:24:57,940
She grew up by the mahjong table.

374
00:24:58,140 --> 00:25:00,180
Eating and sleeping
were all in my game room.

375
00:25:00,500 --> 00:25:01,300
People criticized me

376
00:25:01,355 --> 00:25:03,266
and said that if I did not
raise her properly,

377
00:25:03,333 --> 00:25:04,700
she would turn out badly.

378
00:25:04,700 --> 00:25:05,940
Is that not nonsense?

379
00:25:06,340 --> 00:25:07,577
My daughter is wonderful.

380
00:25:08,060 --> 00:25:08,540
Right?

381
00:25:08,780 --> 00:25:10,060
Now, she is about to get married.

382
00:25:10,660 --> 00:25:12,180
And you're outstanding.

383
00:25:12,300 --> 00:25:14,260
Grandma and I are truly blessed.

384
00:25:14,420 --> 00:25:15,060
Yes.

385
00:25:15,700 --> 00:25:17,220
But I heard from Lanxin

386
00:25:17,700 --> 00:25:19,620
that Ling's
parents are no longer around.

387
00:25:21,180 --> 00:25:22,100
Mr. Zhao,

388
00:25:22,740 --> 00:25:24,260
I have been a burden to my grandson.

389
00:25:24,333 --> 00:25:25,844
Having Grandma, I am already blessed.

390
00:25:26,500 --> 00:25:26,940
Grandma,

391
00:25:27,380 --> 00:25:28,580
I understand what you mean.

392
00:25:28,820 --> 00:25:29,340
Don't worry.

393
00:25:30,300 --> 00:25:31,420
Some families

394
00:25:31,580 --> 00:25:33,060
might care about that,

395
00:25:33,300 --> 00:25:34,300
but ours will not.

396
00:25:35,180 --> 00:25:36,020
I win!

397
00:25:36,460 --> 00:25:36,980
I win!

398
00:25:36,980 --> 00:25:37,560
Alright, then.

399
00:25:37,700 --> 00:25:38,620
I will go ahead first.

400
00:25:38,620 --> 00:25:39,760
- Wait, wait.
- Come back later.

401
00:25:39,780 --> 00:25:40,580
You will understand

402
00:25:41,020 --> 00:25:42,820
Lanxin's value more over time.

403
00:25:42,866 --> 00:25:43,940
Leaving other things aside,

404
00:25:44,180 --> 00:25:46,420
birth, aging, illness, and death,
to put it bluntly,

405
00:25:47,740 --> 00:25:49,180
you will not have to worry at all.

406
00:25:49,620 --> 00:25:50,660
Even your own matters,

407
00:25:50,660 --> 00:25:52,060
- I have finished this round.
- she can help you

408
00:25:52,460 --> 00:25:53,260
- take care of them.
- Sorry about that.

409
00:25:53,500 --> 00:25:54,370
They needed one more player,

410
00:25:54,370 --> 00:25:56,500
so I filled in for a few rounds.
That turned into this long.

411
00:25:56,700 --> 00:25:57,820
Ling Yikai and his grandma.

412
00:25:57,866 --> 00:25:58,460
Mrs. Zhao.

413
00:25:58,555 --> 00:25:59,640
- This is my mom.
- Hello.

414
00:26:00,380 --> 00:26:01,860
Let's take a photo together.

415
00:26:01,888 --> 00:26:02,980
They are still waiting for me next door.

416
00:26:03,060 --> 00:26:03,740
Let's go out together.

417
00:26:03,940 --> 00:26:04,640
- Okay.
- Let's take a photo.

418
00:26:04,660 --> 00:26:05,620
- Ask a waiter to help us.
- Waiter.

419
00:26:05,620 --> 00:26:06,600
Come take a photo for us.

420
00:26:06,620 --> 00:26:06,860
Come.

421
00:26:08,666 --> 00:26:09,520
Not playing anymore?

422
00:26:09,580 --> 00:26:10,420
Wait for me a bit.

423
00:26:15,900 --> 00:26:16,500
Zhao.

424
00:26:17,044 --> 00:26:17,580
What?

425
00:26:17,580 --> 00:26:19,288
I don't know what bad luck I had today.

426
00:26:19,340 --> 00:26:19,920
What happened?

427
00:26:19,933 --> 00:26:21,244
I didn't win a single round. Come.

428
00:26:21,533 --> 00:26:22,777
Give me another 500 yuan.

429
00:26:22,900 --> 00:26:23,380
Okay, okay.

430
00:26:23,422 --> 00:26:25,250
After I eat, I will switch with you.
Don't worry.

431
00:26:25,260 --> 00:26:25,980
Hurry up.

432
00:26:26,260 --> 00:26:26,940
Friends?

433
00:26:27,420 --> 00:26:29,660
Grandma, we are all
familiar neighbors here.

434
00:26:30,740 --> 00:26:31,620
Look here.

435
00:26:32,180 --> 00:26:33,860
Three, two, one.

436
00:26:34,140 --> 00:26:35,300
Cheese.

437
00:26:35,500 --> 00:26:36,980
- Cheese.
- Cheese.

438
00:26:39,133 --> 00:26:40,210
Alright, thank you.

439
00:26:40,210 --> 00:26:40,820
Lanxin.

440
00:26:41,260 --> 00:26:41,780
Grandma.

441
00:26:42,180 --> 00:26:43,540
I want to use the restroom.

442
00:26:43,666 --> 00:26:44,780
- Okay.
- I will take you.

443
00:26:44,940 --> 00:26:45,260
Alright.

444
00:26:45,370 --> 00:26:45,740
Alright.

445
00:26:45,740 --> 00:26:46,180
Let me see.

446
00:26:46,180 --> 00:26:46,888
There are steps.

447
00:26:47,260 --> 00:26:47,740
Sit, Ling.

448
00:26:49,700 --> 00:26:51,380
Grandma does not know we are divorced?

449
00:26:52,420 --> 00:26:52,860
Divorced?

450
00:26:53,940 --> 00:26:54,820
You did not know?

451
00:26:56,140 --> 00:26:57,660
Lanxin never mentioned it, huh?

452
00:26:57,660 --> 00:26:58,980
Why bring that up?

453
00:26:59,580 --> 00:27:00,580
It was a long time ago.

454
00:27:03,100 --> 00:27:03,740
Let me tell you.

455
00:27:04,020 --> 00:27:05,020
We are divorced.

456
00:27:05,500 --> 00:27:06,660
We both remarried.

457
00:27:07,300 --> 00:27:08,140
That woman just now

458
00:27:08,220 --> 00:27:09,740
is his current wife.

459
00:27:10,220 --> 00:27:12,500
My partner is also playing cards nearby.

460
00:27:13,180 --> 00:27:14,500
Anyway, after going around,

461
00:27:14,500 --> 00:27:16,660
we are all just players
from the game room.

462
00:27:17,420 --> 00:27:18,460
We did think about

463
00:27:18,580 --> 00:27:19,820
splitting up the business.

464
00:27:20,300 --> 00:27:21,460
But it was doing well.

465
00:27:21,688 --> 00:27:22,555
So we discussed it

466
00:27:22,600 --> 00:27:24,410
and decided to continue together,
half and half.

467
00:27:24,420 --> 00:27:25,620
You all get along quite well.

468
00:27:26,740 --> 00:27:27,460
Not bad.

469
00:27:28,060 --> 00:27:30,140
Zhao Lanxin keeps
an eye on things for us.

470
00:27:30,140 --> 00:27:32,300
How the money
is divided is all up to her.

471
00:27:32,700 --> 00:27:33,540
Do you know why?

472
00:27:33,610 --> 00:27:35,620
She is the legal
representative of the game room.

473
00:27:35,700 --> 00:27:36,940
We are all just employees.

474
00:27:39,111 --> 00:27:40,860
She is not someone
who cares about money.

475
00:27:41,100 --> 00:27:44,620
She just likes managing money,
people, and affairs.

476
00:27:45,140 --> 00:27:47,340
Isn't she taking
good care of your grandma now?

477
00:27:47,420 --> 00:27:47,740
Yes.

478
00:27:48,340 --> 00:27:48,660
Yes.

479
00:27:53,140 --> 00:27:56,740
(Jinbei Law Firm)

480
00:28:21,866 --> 00:28:22,500
Come on in.

481
00:28:22,740 --> 00:28:23,220
Lawyer Bei.

482
00:28:24,755 --> 00:28:26,288
What did you want to see me about?

483
00:28:27,111 --> 00:28:29,111
About the transfer to
the Southwest Branch,

484
00:28:29,180 --> 00:28:29,820
I have decided.

485
00:28:30,260 --> 00:28:30,660
I will go.

486
00:28:31,311 --> 00:28:34,010
Didn't you say before
that you didn't want to leave Shanghai

487
00:28:34,010 --> 00:28:35,711
and didn't want
a long-distance relationship?

488
00:28:35,940 --> 00:28:37,260
Why the sudden change?

489
00:28:38,340 --> 00:28:38,780
Yes.

490
00:28:40,020 --> 00:28:40,700
So I thought

491
00:28:40,977 --> 00:28:42,533
I would propose to Zhou Mei first.

492
00:28:42,620 --> 00:28:43,980
After we get engaged, I will go.

493
00:28:46,260 --> 00:28:47,220
Have you told her?

494
00:28:47,780 --> 00:28:48,340
Not yet.

495
00:28:48,940 --> 00:28:49,740
I was just about to.

496
00:28:51,380 --> 00:28:53,220
What if she does not agree?

497
00:28:56,020 --> 00:28:57,020
That is why I hope

498
00:28:57,380 --> 00:28:58,955
you can come with me to persuade her.

499
00:29:02,060 --> 00:29:03,100
You mean

500
00:29:04,420 --> 00:29:05,666
you want me to go with you?

501
00:29:06,780 --> 00:29:07,860
As my supervisor

502
00:29:08,220 --> 00:29:08,900
and mentor,

503
00:29:09,244 --> 00:29:11,977
you can explain to her the importance
of my going to the Southwest Branch.

504
00:29:12,940 --> 00:29:13,940
You can also tell her

505
00:29:14,300 --> 00:29:14,980
to feel at ease

506
00:29:15,133 --> 00:29:16,355
and wait for me to come back.

507
00:29:20,580 --> 00:29:22,444
I really hope you can help me with this.

508
00:29:22,900 --> 00:29:23,940
Because for me,

509
00:29:24,340 --> 00:29:25,660
this is the best of both worlds.

510
00:29:31,980 --> 00:29:33,180
Please set up a time with her.

511
00:29:33,422 --> 00:29:34,777
Thank you, Lawyer Bei.

512
00:29:35,500 --> 00:29:36,555
I'll leave you to it.

513
00:29:49,460 --> 00:29:50,020
Grandma,

514
00:29:50,540 --> 00:29:52,300
have you withdrawn
your pension this month?

515
00:29:52,860 --> 00:29:53,380
I have.

516
00:29:53,900 --> 00:29:55,220
Zhao helped me withdraw it.

517
00:29:56,420 --> 00:29:58,180
Grandma said she asked you before,

518
00:29:58,300 --> 00:29:59,780
but you kept delaying for days.

519
00:30:00,980 --> 00:30:02,980
Then you should
keep this bank card safe.

520
00:30:03,022 --> 00:30:04,244
Don't leave it lying around,

521
00:30:04,266 --> 00:30:05,620
or you will panic if it gets lost.

522
00:30:05,780 --> 00:30:06,220
Alright?

523
00:30:07,140 --> 00:30:07,820
I will not.

524
00:30:08,220 --> 00:30:09,740
Zhao is keeping it for me.

525
00:30:10,420 --> 00:30:11,060
From now on,

526
00:30:11,580 --> 00:30:12,860
she will withdraw it for me.

527
00:30:13,420 --> 00:30:15,980
I have given her
my medical card and everything.

528
00:30:17,100 --> 00:30:18,460
If I need them, I will go to her.

529
00:30:27,660 --> 00:30:28,500
The bank card,

530
00:30:28,911 --> 00:30:29,740
the medical card,

531
00:30:29,977 --> 00:30:31,088
and what else?

532
00:30:31,266 --> 00:30:32,600
Give them back to me.

533
00:30:33,511 --> 00:30:34,400
They are at my place.

534
00:30:34,460 --> 00:30:35,355
Do you need them now?

535
00:30:35,622 --> 00:30:37,333
Come with me, and I'll get them for you.

536
00:30:47,220 --> 00:30:48,140
This is the passbook.

537
00:30:48,380 --> 00:30:50,460
On this note are
the dates for meter readings

538
00:30:50,460 --> 00:30:51,540
and the payment dates.

539
00:30:51,622 --> 00:30:53,300
You can link the payments to your phone

540
00:30:53,300 --> 00:30:54,444
for automatic payment.

541
00:30:54,533 --> 00:30:55,866
This is for social security.

542
00:30:55,870 --> 00:30:57,733
The regular schedule
and location for medication

543
00:30:57,740 --> 00:30:58,380
are all written here.

544
00:30:58,380 --> 00:31:00,370
Some medicines are not covered, so you
have to buy them at the pharmacy.

545
00:31:00,380 --> 00:31:02,466
I have written where
to buy them as well.

546
00:31:02,540 --> 00:31:05,300
Follow-up visits require
an online appointment in advance

547
00:31:05,600 --> 00:31:07,622
with the time, department,
and doctor selected.

548
00:31:07,666 --> 00:31:09,622
You will also need the senior card,
right?

549
00:31:10,020 --> 00:31:10,940
The community office

550
00:31:10,940 --> 00:31:12,644
- will come by to help clean.
- Okay.

551
00:31:13,466 --> 00:31:15,155
Keep these with you for now.

552
00:31:18,180 --> 00:31:19,020
Do you think

553
00:31:19,244 --> 00:31:20,622
I am after the elderly's money?

554
00:31:20,700 --> 00:31:22,380
How could you care
about this little amount?

555
00:31:23,060 --> 00:31:24,580
I genuinely want to help you.

556
00:31:28,111 --> 00:31:29,000
You already have.

557
00:31:31,700 --> 00:31:33,610
The elderly hesitate to see specialists,

558
00:31:33,610 --> 00:31:35,555
and they are reluctant
to buy imported medicine.

559
00:31:35,620 --> 00:31:36,660
I paid for it myself.

560
00:31:40,340 --> 00:31:40,740
Thank you.

561
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:43,355
I will give it to you.

562
00:31:43,500 --> 00:31:45,020
You know that is not what I want.

563
00:31:45,860 --> 00:31:47,300
I want you to truly feel I matter.

564
00:31:57,540 --> 00:31:57,940
I do.

565
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:01,533
How do you want me to show it?

566
00:32:02,660 --> 00:32:04,300
If you really think I matter,

567
00:32:05,140 --> 00:32:06,180
then propose to me.

568
00:32:06,700 --> 00:32:07,180
Marry me.

569
00:32:07,180 --> 00:32:08,020
Is that not too fast?

570
00:32:08,620 --> 00:32:09,500
Too fast.

571
00:32:10,044 --> 00:32:11,911
We have already met
each other's parents.

572
00:32:12,066 --> 00:32:14,066
At least, give me some time to prepare.

573
00:32:17,740 --> 00:32:19,020
Don't make me wait too long.

574
00:32:22,644 --> 00:32:24,488
You really keep
everything in separate bags.

575
00:32:25,133 --> 00:32:27,100
It is easier to manage
and not mix things up.

576
00:32:27,860 --> 00:32:28,700
This is my dad's.

577
00:32:29,420 --> 00:32:30,140
This is my mom's.

578
00:32:33,422 --> 00:32:35,180
There will be one more for you,
Ling Yikai.

579
00:32:38,660 --> 00:32:40,060
Don't push me too hard.

580
00:33:08,860 --> 00:33:09,860
Such a big setup.

581
00:33:10,300 --> 00:33:11,820
You even brought Lawyer Bei.

582
00:33:12,180 --> 00:33:14,060
He is not easy to invite.

583
00:33:15,900 --> 00:33:18,140
I am here as support today.

584
00:33:24,340 --> 00:33:24,900
What is wrong?

585
00:33:27,060 --> 00:33:28,460
It is just a two-year transfer.

586
00:33:28,460 --> 00:33:29,733
I already said I support you.

587
00:33:35,060 --> 00:33:35,740
Say it.

588
00:33:37,020 --> 00:33:38,555
If you don't, I will say it for you?

589
00:33:39,060 --> 00:33:39,540
No, no.

590
00:33:39,860 --> 00:33:40,940
I invited more support.

591
00:33:41,340 --> 00:33:41,940
Let's wait.

592
00:33:46,980 --> 00:33:47,420
Mrs. Bei.

593
00:33:48,740 --> 00:33:49,180
Mrs. Bei.

594
00:33:51,060 --> 00:33:51,980
Sorry.

595
00:33:52,380 --> 00:33:53,980
I am late for something this important.

596
00:33:55,740 --> 00:33:56,940
So, where are you now?

597
00:33:57,140 --> 00:33:57,940
Have you started?

598
00:33:59,888 --> 00:34:02,377
You never inform me in advance
when you bring your wife.

599
00:34:04,220 --> 00:34:04,820
Zhang Yousen,

600
00:34:05,740 --> 00:34:07,820
you invited my wife as support,

601
00:34:08,100 --> 00:34:09,180
and you did not tell me?

602
00:34:10,060 --> 00:34:11,180
The more, the merrier.

603
00:34:11,900 --> 00:34:13,580
Yousen is like family to us.

604
00:34:13,860 --> 00:34:16,020
For his future, I have to show support.

605
00:34:16,533 --> 00:34:17,700
Of course, I had to come.

606
00:34:19,500 --> 00:34:20,700
This is a lot.

607
00:34:20,900 --> 00:34:22,422
You are putting me under pressure.

608
00:34:22,533 --> 00:34:24,711
Dating has turned into
something for four people.

609
00:34:26,580 --> 00:34:28,100
We are just here to accompany.

610
00:34:28,420 --> 00:34:29,540
It is mainly up to you.

611
00:34:29,740 --> 00:34:30,900
Right, everyone is here now.

612
00:34:31,540 --> 00:34:32,140
I will say it.

613
00:34:33,020 --> 00:34:33,380
Zhou Mei,

614
00:34:33,688 --> 00:34:35,500
about my transfer to
the Southwest Branch,

615
00:34:35,620 --> 00:34:37,060
Lawyer Bei wants me to go next month.

616
00:34:38,100 --> 00:34:40,000
So I hope you can
wait for me for two years.

617
00:34:42,288 --> 00:34:42,940
I cannot wait.

618
00:34:45,266 --> 00:34:47,220
No matter who asks me,
my answer is the same.

619
00:34:48,340 --> 00:34:49,700
A lot can change in two years.

620
00:34:50,733 --> 00:34:52,180
Two years ago, you did not know me,

621
00:34:52,622 --> 00:34:54,540
and in two years,
I don't know who I will meet.

622
00:34:55,355 --> 00:34:56,380
So I cannot lie to you.

623
00:35:05,180 --> 00:35:06,820
That is one way to look at it,

624
00:35:07,660 --> 00:35:08,860
but Yousen just said it, too.

625
00:35:09,180 --> 00:35:10,740
It is just his wish.

626
00:35:11,140 --> 00:35:12,820
You can also treat it as a wish.

627
00:35:13,422 --> 00:35:14,820
There may be many uncertainties,

628
00:35:15,460 --> 00:35:16,860
but having a shared wish

629
00:35:17,140 --> 00:35:18,500
is better than having none, right?

630
00:35:19,220 --> 00:35:19,780
Yes.

631
00:35:20,866 --> 00:35:22,960
It is not like he will not
come back for two years.

632
00:35:23,220 --> 00:35:24,111
There are holidays

633
00:35:24,420 --> 00:35:25,020
and weekends,

634
00:35:25,380 --> 00:35:25,700
right?

635
00:35:26,540 --> 00:35:28,980
Chengdu, Chongqing, and Guiyang are only

636
00:35:28,980 --> 00:35:30,600
about a three-hour flight from Shanghai.

637
00:35:30,700 --> 00:35:33,266
Nowadays, many people travel back
and forth for work between two cities.

638
00:35:33,333 --> 00:35:34,377
It is very normal.

639
00:35:34,540 --> 00:35:35,140
Besides,

640
00:35:35,540 --> 00:35:36,580
as the saying goes,

641
00:35:37,020 --> 00:35:39,940
when two people love each other,
distance does not matter.

642
00:35:43,380 --> 00:35:43,700
Right?

643
00:35:44,577 --> 00:35:45,711
Zhang Yousen,

644
00:35:45,777 --> 00:35:47,111
you need to be more of a man.

645
00:35:47,220 --> 00:35:49,020
You cannot put all
the pressure on Zhou Mei.

646
00:35:49,580 --> 00:35:52,780
You need to put in the effort

647
00:35:52,940 --> 00:35:54,500
to maintain

648
00:35:54,666 --> 00:35:56,133
your relationship for these two years.

649
00:35:56,580 --> 00:35:56,980
Yes.

650
00:35:57,420 --> 00:35:58,580
I did not ask it well enough.

651
00:35:59,822 --> 00:36:00,620
It is alright.

652
00:36:00,980 --> 00:36:02,220
Let's move past that question.

653
00:36:02,780 --> 00:36:05,540
There is something
more important ahead, right?

654
00:36:17,580 --> 00:36:17,980
Zhou Mei,

655
00:36:20,700 --> 00:36:21,580
before I leave,

656
00:36:25,300 --> 00:36:26,820
I hope you will accept my proposal.

657
00:36:31,180 --> 00:36:32,180
Such a big diamond ring,

658
00:36:33,222 --> 00:36:34,822
where did you get the money to buy it?

659
00:36:48,100 --> 00:36:48,780
Well,

660
00:36:49,060 --> 00:36:50,540
Yousen borrowed money from me.

661
00:36:51,200 --> 00:36:52,820
He insisted on buying you a big one.

662
00:36:52,980 --> 00:36:54,555
He said a small one would not suit you.

663
00:36:54,580 --> 00:36:56,020
So, on behalf of Lawyer Bei,

664
00:36:56,260 --> 00:36:57,620
I advanced his salary to him.

665
00:36:58,220 --> 00:36:58,940
You could say

666
00:36:59,180 --> 00:37:01,140
this is the boss contributing

667
00:37:01,140 --> 00:37:02,480
to an employee's happiness. Right?

668
00:37:13,060 --> 00:37:13,911
Stand up first.

669
00:37:20,180 --> 00:37:20,820
Stand up.

670
00:37:24,020 --> 00:37:24,980
Don't play games,

671
00:37:24,980 --> 00:37:27,022
like you will not get up
unless I say yes.

672
00:37:27,822 --> 00:37:29,400
I really dislike that.

673
00:37:33,620 --> 00:37:34,060
Yousen,

674
00:37:35,533 --> 00:37:36,888
you have made the proposal.

675
00:37:36,977 --> 00:37:38,777
Whether Zhou Mei accepts is up to her.

676
00:37:39,060 --> 00:37:39,980
Come back and sit down.

677
00:37:41,780 --> 00:37:43,060
Come, sit.

678
00:37:54,940 --> 00:37:55,700
I originally wanted

679
00:37:55,980 --> 00:37:57,380
Mrs. Bei and Lawyer Bei

680
00:37:57,380 --> 00:37:58,340
to be witnesses.

681
00:37:59,380 --> 00:38:00,220
If you agreed,

682
00:38:01,333 --> 00:38:04,133
Lawyer Bei would also feel at ease
about my going to Chengdu.

683
00:38:04,822 --> 00:38:06,533
But since you don't agree now,

684
00:38:08,020 --> 00:38:09,060
I am still hesitating

685
00:38:09,300 --> 00:38:10,340
whether to go or not.

686
00:38:14,660 --> 00:38:15,340
Yousen

687
00:38:15,780 --> 00:38:17,740
is a very promising young man.

688
00:38:19,260 --> 00:38:20,740
When I married Lawyer Bei,

689
00:38:21,020 --> 00:38:22,700
he was not even as
outstanding as Yousen.

690
00:38:23,900 --> 00:38:24,780
In two years,

691
00:38:25,044 --> 00:38:26,133
when he returns,

692
00:38:26,540 --> 00:38:27,940
his future will be limitless.

693
00:38:29,940 --> 00:38:31,500
So, Lawyer Bei, what you mean

694
00:38:31,688 --> 00:38:33,933
is that in two years, the one
who changes will not be me,

695
00:38:33,940 --> 00:38:34,780
but Zhang Yousen.

696
00:38:35,660 --> 00:38:38,380
So I should accept this ring now, right?

697
00:38:44,140 --> 00:38:45,500
I think you should accept the ring

698
00:38:46,260 --> 00:38:47,500
to put Yousen at ease.

699
00:38:50,980 --> 00:38:52,180
Once Yousen is at ease,

700
00:38:53,311 --> 00:38:54,780
Lawyer Bei will also be at ease.

701
00:38:55,900 --> 00:38:56,380
Right?

702
00:39:03,460 --> 00:39:03,780
Well...

703
00:39:08,060 --> 00:39:08,700
Yeah,

704
00:39:09,020 --> 00:39:10,740
I feel that if Zhang Yousen

705
00:39:10,740 --> 00:39:12,580
does not go to Chengdu,

706
00:39:12,580 --> 00:39:13,900
it will be troublesome for me.

707
00:39:14,140 --> 00:39:15,555
I would not know who to send.

708
00:39:15,700 --> 00:39:16,580
Someone capable

709
00:39:17,020 --> 00:39:17,860
and willing to go.

710
00:39:20,820 --> 00:39:23,540
So, did Lawyer Bei bring us together

711
00:39:24,340 --> 00:39:26,100
because we are compatible

712
00:39:26,540 --> 00:39:28,100
or for the company's arrangements?

713
00:39:31,580 --> 00:39:32,900
Both, I think.

714
00:39:33,580 --> 00:39:35,020
Where do you think we are compatible?

715
00:39:39,940 --> 00:39:41,220
What if I have other options?

716
00:39:44,980 --> 00:39:45,580
You...

717
00:39:46,100 --> 00:39:47,700
You are publicly a couple,

718
00:39:47,980 --> 00:39:48,300
right?

719
00:39:48,540 --> 00:39:50,900
You look very compatible,
very well-matched.

720
00:39:51,220 --> 00:39:53,940
And you have a promising future.

721
00:39:58,700 --> 00:40:00,140
More importantly,

722
00:40:00,700 --> 00:40:02,660
Zhang Yousen

723
00:40:03,860 --> 00:40:05,500
is wholeheartedly devoted to you.

724
00:40:32,420 --> 00:40:32,900
Yousen,

725
00:40:35,340 --> 00:40:35,780
first,

726
00:40:37,155 --> 00:40:39,466
you did not need to buy
such a big diamond ring.

727
00:40:39,622 --> 00:40:40,620
Whether I accept or not

728
00:40:40,620 --> 00:40:41,940
has nothing to do with its size.

729
00:40:42,860 --> 00:40:44,100
It is just an accessory.

730
00:40:45,500 --> 00:40:45,860
Second,

731
00:40:46,740 --> 00:40:47,660
I will not accept

732
00:40:47,780 --> 00:40:49,540
just because you brought

733
00:40:49,540 --> 00:40:50,860
Lawyer Bei and Mrs. Bei here.

734
00:40:51,820 --> 00:40:52,740
Instead, I feel

735
00:40:53,822 --> 00:40:55,111
you are trying to corner me.

736
00:40:59,980 --> 00:41:00,420
Third,

737
00:41:01,066 --> 00:41:02,711
I am not ready to get married.

738
00:41:02,977 --> 00:41:04,555
It has nothing to do with the ring.

739
00:41:05,022 --> 00:41:06,600
Marriage needs to be taken seriously.

740
00:41:07,140 --> 00:41:07,940
We are only dating.

741
00:41:11,244 --> 00:41:13,222
If we don't have money,
we buy something cheaper.

742
00:41:13,244 --> 00:41:15,155
If we have money later,
we can buy something better.

743
00:41:15,420 --> 00:41:16,300
If I accept

744
00:41:16,300 --> 00:41:18,333
this ring bought with
Lawyer Bei's money,

745
00:41:19,220 --> 00:41:20,060
then whose sincerity

746
00:41:20,620 --> 00:41:21,340
does it represent?

747
00:41:31,888 --> 00:41:33,622
Regarding the company arrangements,

748
00:41:33,911 --> 00:41:35,133
you can continue talking.

749
00:41:35,380 --> 00:41:36,355
I will leave first.

750
00:42:04,940 --> 00:42:10,740
♪If the sky and the sea
turned upside down♪

751
00:42:12,460 --> 00:42:18,220
♪If a swimming fish fell
in love with a flying bird♪

752
00:42:19,900 --> 00:42:26,620
♪If back then we had never let go♪

753
00:42:27,380 --> 00:42:32,580
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

754
00:42:34,660 --> 00:42:36,780
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

755
00:42:37,020 --> 00:42:38,620
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

756
00:42:38,860 --> 00:42:41,340
♪And found our way back whole♪

757
00:42:42,100 --> 00:42:44,220
♪So let this surging love♪

758
00:42:44,460 --> 00:42:48,740
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

759
00:42:49,740 --> 00:42:52,740
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain,
that's alright♪

760
00:42:53,460 --> 00:42:56,460
♪If we're buried by passing years,
all the better♪

761
00:42:57,140 --> 00:42:59,300
♪At least we still can keep♪

762
00:42:59,500 --> 00:43:03,700
♪This one eternal photograph♪

763
00:43:03,700 --> 00:43:04,060
Hello.

764
00:43:05,921 --> 00:43:07,041
(I've been thinking.)

765
00:43:08,321 --> 00:43:11,601
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

766
00:43:12,361 --> 00:43:19,691
(is probably different.)

767
00:43:20,691 --> 00:43:22,441
♪If the sky♪

768
00:43:22,951 --> 00:43:24,351
♪And the sea♪

769
00:43:24,891 --> 00:43:26,601
♪Turned upside down♪

770
00:43:28,161 --> 00:43:30,091
♪If a swimming fish♪

771
00:43:30,491 --> 00:43:33,881
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

772
00:43:35,651 --> 00:43:37,621
♪If back then♪

773
00:43:37,981 --> 00:43:42,391
♪We had never let go♪

774
00:43:42,991 --> 00:43:49,271
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

775
00:43:50,391 --> 00:43:52,541
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

776
00:43:52,541 --> 00:43:54,411
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

777
00:43:54,591 --> 00:43:57,031
♪And found our way back whole♪

778
00:43:57,871 --> 00:44:00,041
♪So let this surging love♪

779
00:44:00,041 --> 00:44:04,471
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

780
00:44:05,371 --> 00:44:07,551
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

781
00:44:07,551 --> 00:44:08,641
♪That's alright♪

782
00:44:09,181 --> 00:44:09,931
♪If we're buried♪

783
00:44:09,931 --> 00:44:12,631
♪By passing years all the better♪

784
00:44:12,891 --> 00:44:15,071
♪At least we still can keep♪

785
00:44:15,251 --> 00:44:19,671
♪This one eternal photograph♪

786
00:44:35,431 --> 00:44:37,721
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

787
00:44:37,721 --> 00:44:39,481
♪Running in opposite ways♪

788
00:44:39,601 --> 00:44:42,071
♪Searching all along the way♪

789
00:44:42,871 --> 00:44:45,031
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

790
00:44:45,221 --> 00:44:50,131
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

791
00:44:50,131 --> 00:44:53,651
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

792
00:44:53,891 --> 00:44:54,861
♪Only after loss♪

793
00:44:54,861 --> 00:44:57,491
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

794
00:44:57,901 --> 00:45:00,261
♪In another time and space♪

795
00:45:00,261 --> 00:45:01,821
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

796
00:45:01,821 --> 00:45:04,651
♪Till we grow old♪

797
00:45:05,611 --> 00:45:07,901
♪But still the sky will never♪

798
00:45:07,901 --> 00:45:10,571
♪Turn with the sea♪

799
00:45:13,091 --> 00:45:15,501
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

800
00:45:15,501 --> 00:45:20,711
♪Fall in love with a flying bird♪
